Orchid Forest Cikole 🥰✨ Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on nomadfervor.com (link in my bio: @nomadfervor)

Projected to be the largest orchid forest in Indonesia 😍 Its location is surrounded by 12 hectares of protected forest filled with pine trees. There are now 157 species of orchids from Indonesia, United States, Peru and Venezuela.

📸 @warmanwardhani
📍 Orchid Forest Cikole, Indonesia

node.text:
The best leg ever 🐶🦵Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @nomadfervor

Tag someone who has to see this!

This is the story of Andrea Pusateri, a paralympic athlete and his adorable dog Sally:

"At the age of three and a half, I escaped from my mother’s hands while a train was passing at the Monza’s train station. She laid down her life to save me and I lost both of my legs, but the doctors were able to reimplant my left leg with an operation. When I was a child, I practiced several sports until I run into the bicycle. In 2008, I began my agonistic carrier in the Paralympic world, where I achieved several results at a national and international level."

How awe-inspiring is Andrea's story? 🐶

📽 @pusateriandrea #nature
📍Cancano Lake, Italy
🎶 Tommee Profitt - In The End (Mellen Gi Remix) [feat. Fleurie]

node.text:
Villa del Soffio 🏡 We can promote your photos in our account. Check the link in our bio for instructions: @nomadfervor

An experimental home niched in the cliffs of #Puglia. The structure acts as a bridge between both sides of the beach allowing for a generous double height space with a minimal footprint in the natural landscape. The house is composed of two slabs glazed on each side, overlooking the raw vertical cliffs to the west and the Adriatic sea to the east.

The interior layout works as one continuous space with no interruptions and punctuated by two layers of curtains where privacy is needed. A first layer on the open mezzanine overlooking the living spaces, and a second double height layer all around the house. This project questions the relationship we entertain with our environment by reimagining the shape and foundation of the house itself.

Designed by @CharlotteTaylr & @NicholasPreaud

Spotting sea snakes with @brodiemoss 😱 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @nomadfervor

“Sea snakes normally avoid humans but this time of year they become very active, sexually frustrated and potentially aggressive as they search for a mate 🐍 like this old fella who appeared from the ocean floor and followed me around on my paddle board before disappearing 😅”

What would you do in this situation? 😱

📽 @brodiemoss
📍Australia
